	quest.56C8741E7E094319.quest_desc: ["The Calibrated Precision Mechanism is a specialized fusion of Create engineering and Ars Nouveau magic. By infusing a standard mechanism with magical properties, you unlock the ability to craft advanced devices from the Ars Technica expansion."]
	quest.56C8741E7E094319.quest_subtitle: "Calibrated With Magic?!?"
	quest.5776282EB4D1EDFE.quest_subtitle: "Smells Like Despair (and Power)"
	quest.58FCE7A369122D5A.quest_subtitle: "Flying Machines Optional"
	quest.58FCE7A369122D5A.title: "END"
	quest.5951EA51E457E585.quest_desc: [
		"The Brass Machine is the final and most advanced casing of the early industrial era. By combining a Precision Mechanism with a Brass Casing, you create a high-performance machine base capable of complex logic and rapid motion."
		""
		"What it does: This is the essential chassis for \"smart\" automation. You will need these to craft the Rotation Speed Controller, Mechanical Arms, and Stockpile Switches. It’s the key to making your factory run itself!"
		""
		"While you can start by crafting these manually, they can be produced much more efficiently using Sequenced Assembly. Setting up a line of Deployers will save you resources and time as you scale up your factory!"
	]
	quest.5951EA51E457E585.quest_subtitle: "Engineering Goals"
	quest.59840E17442DFD40.quest_subtitle: "Easy Trading"
	quest.59A27C7BD890F8D6.quest_subtitle: "TP HOME"
	quest.5BDA779C367F392E.quest_desc: [
		"&l&oWait... but I don't have Brass?&r&r"
		""
		"Don't worry! While standard Deployers usually require Brass, you can jumpstart your automation much earlier. By crafting a Zinc Hand instead of a Brass one, you can create \"Early-Game\" Deployers."
		""
		"This allows you to set up Sequenced Assembly lines long before you ever smell a Blaze Burner. Use this trick to mass-produce your Mechanisms and Machines with much higher efficiency!"
	]
