	quest.77D17A763D29BDB2.quest_subtitle: "Fancy Wireless Player Charging"
	quest.794911A3AA6DAB2A.quest_desc: [
		"The Player Access block bridges your inventory to a Depot for charging. By enabling \"&lRespect Data&r\" on a Create filter, the system can distinguish between empty and full gear. "
		""
		"This allows you to automatically pull drained items, hold them until the NBT matches your \"Full\" requirement, and then cycle them back into your defined inventory slots."
	]
	quest.794911A3AA6DAB2A.quest_subtitle: "Wireless Charging Automation"
	quest.7987F94F9852E859.quest_subtitle: "No TIME To WAIT"
	quest.7A09A8746EB33C29.quest_desc: [
		"The Copper Mechanism is the heart of the Steam Age. It represents a shift from simple kinetics to fluid management and advanced thermodynamics."
		""
		"What it does: This mechanism is the essential component for crafting Copper Machines (Casings). More importantly, it is a key ingredient in creating Blaze Bloom Goo, which is vital for progressing toward heat-based processing and beyond."
		""
		"While you can start by crafting these manually, they can be produced much more efficiently using Sequenced Assembly. Setting up a line of Deployers will save you resources and time as you scale up your factory!"
	]
	quest.7A09A8746EB33C29.quest_subtitle: "Shiny New Problems"
	quest.7B24ABF5482FEB31.quest_subtitle: "Must Be Voided and Beamed Up"
	quest.7C53EFB85442DD4A.quest_subtitle: "Wait... The one from Quark?!?"
	quest.7C613795F2976618.quest_desc: ["The same mastery that allows you to manifest Archwood trees applies to the magical flora of the world. You no longer need to rely on rare finds or complex synthesis; you can now craft the seeds of magical sustenance yourself!"]
	quest.7C613795F2976618.quest_subtitle: "No Trees Harmed"
	quest.7E0359DA69355E78.quest_subtitle: "Rest in pieces. Literally."
	quest.7E74969D28BD3C2D.quest_desc: ["The Ender Source Jar is the pinnacle of magical storage from Ars Additions. It solves the biggest headache for any magical engineer: logistics. Instead of manually moving jars or piping liquid source across kilometers of factory floor, the Ender Source Jar uses the power of the void to keep your mana accessible everywhere."]
	quest.7E74969D28BD3C2D.quest_subtitle: "Dimensionally Convenient"
	quest.7ED244FD96FC1968.quest_subtitle: "It Smells Like Sulfur"
	quest.7ED244FD96FC1968.title: "NETHER"
	quest.7EF145F224EDF6C8.quest_desc: ["&fInto a BEAM of LIGHT!&r"]
	quest.7EF145F224EDF6C8.quest_subtitle: "Literally Just Light"
	quest.7F9E8DE361216AF7.quest_desc: [
		"First Make a &lBudding Time Crystal&r by Infecting Budding Amethyst with Goo!"
		""
		""
		"&lThe Automation Loop&r:"
		""
		"&l&bCharge (Overworld)&r&r: Place the Budding Block in the Overworld until it turns Blue (Stage 1)."
		""
		"&l&6Charge (Nether)&r&r: Move it to the Nether until it turns Orange (Stage 2)."
		""
		"&l&2Charge \\& Harvest (The End)&r&r: Move it to The End. It will turn Green (Stage 3) and begin growing crystals."
		""
		"&lReset&r: Once the energy is spent and the block turns dark again, move it back to the Overworld to restart the cycle."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&lThe Tools You’ll Need&r:"
		""
		"&lAdvanced Sensor&r: Set to detect the NBT \"Stage\" of the Budding Block (0, 1, 2, or 3)."
		""
		"&lAdvanced Swapper&r: Linked to another Swapper in a different dimension to teleport the block automatically when the Sensor triggers."
		""
		"&lAdvanced Block Breaker&r: Configured with a filter to only break the Time Crystal Cluster and not the Budding Block itself."
		""
		"&o&dNote: You cannot mine the Budding Block (even with Silk Touch) without it shattering. Use the Advanced Swapper or a Cut Paste Gadget to move it safely!&r&r"
	]
